    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-03-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-03-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="170"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d170">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Denby.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-03-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 8, 1894</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 865.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received your No. 1775, of the 30th
                    December last, and the copy which you inclosed of your reply to the Yamên on the
                    subject of travelers reporting en route to the local authorities. The views of
                    the Department, which accord with your own, were contained in an instruction
                    (No. 852<note n="*" xml:id="d170fn1">Printed in <ref target="frus1893#pg_244"
                            >Foreign Relations, 1893, p. 244</ref>.</note> of 27th December last)
                    sent you at or near the date of your dispatch.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
